MALACAÑANG Manila

PROCLAMATION NO . 519

RESERVING FOR THE USE OF THE BUREAU OF CUSTOMS, PORT OF PULUPANDAN A CERTAIN PARCEL OF LAND OF THE PUBLIC DOMAIN LOCATED IN THE MUNICIPALITY OF PULUPANDAN, PROVINCE OF NEGROS OCCIDENTAL, ISLAND OF NEGROS

Upon recommendation of the Secretary of Environment and Natural Resources and by virtue of the powers vested in me by law, I, GLORIA MACAPAGAL -ARROYO , President of the Philippines, do hereby withdraw from sale or any other forms of disposition, and reserve for use of the Bureau of Customs, Port of Pulupandan, under the administration of the Bureau of Customs, subject to private rights, if any there be, a certain parcel of land of the public domain, located at Barangay Zone 5, Pulupandan, Negros Occidental, Island of Negros, which parcel of land is more particularly described as follows:

Ng-06-000026

A PARCEL OF LAND (Ng-06-000026) (proposed reservation for the Bureau of Customs Port of Pulupandan) situated in Poblacion, Municipality of Pulupandan, Province of Negros Occidental, Island of Negros. Bounded on the NE, along line 1-2 by Lot 1179-B, along line 2-3 by Lot 1177, on the SE., along line 3-4 by Public Land, all of Valladolid Cad. 42., along line 4-5 by MLA-06-03-002809; on the SW., along 5-6 by Public Land (claimed by Philippine Ports Authority); on NW., along line 6-7 by Road (15.00 meters wide); and on the NE., along line 7-1 by Lot 1179-A, Valladolid Cad 42. Beginning at a point marked “1” on plan being N. 57 deg. 20 W, 680.43 meters from BLLM No. 2, Cad 42, Valladolid cadastre to corner “1” thence.

33.94 m. to point 2;

27.93 m. to point 3;

11.84 m. to point 4;

2.07 m. to point 5;

71.57 m. to point 6;

31.74 m. to point 7;

13.54 m. to point of

beginning containing an area of ONE THOUSAND FIVE HUNDRED (1,500) square meters , more or less. All corners referred to are indicated on the plan and are marked on the ground as follows: point 1 & 2 by Old Points and the rest by PS. Cycl. Mons. 15×40 cm. Bearings true, surveyed by Engr. Gonzalo C. Robles on August 22, 1997, and approved on September 4, 1998.

The parcel of land herein reserved shall be non-alienable and shall not be subject to occupation, entry, sale, lease, or other disposition until again declared alienable by Proclamation of the President.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF , I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

DONE in the City of Manila, this 17 th day of December, in the year of Our Lord, Two Thousand and Three.

(Sgd.) GLORIA MACAPAGAL-ARROYO

By the President: (Sgd.) ALBERTO G. ROMULO Executive Secretary

